        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>May 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Ogle</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I think the “Die Befruchtung der Blumen durch Insekten by D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. H. Müller 1873 Leipzig” (1 vol. with 478 pages), would be well worth your getting; for besides many excellent original observations, it seems a perfect index for Germany &amp; Italy of all that has been done.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 (1 … with)] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi>; ‘with’ <hi rend="italic">after interl del</hi> ‘in’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 478] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘p.’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5698.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">H. Müller 1873</ref>. CD was reading the book in May 1873 (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8901.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Hermann Müller, 5 May 1873</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Ogle had published three papers on the fertilisation of plants (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5942.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ogle 1869</ref>, 1870a, and 1870b). CD had lent Ogle a paper on this topic; see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 16, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6346.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from William Ogle, 2 September 1868</ref>. <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5698.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">H. Müller 1873</ref>, pp. 3–27, included a review of all the literature on the subject.</note>
        </div>        
            
